# ============================================================================
# _rs3ctl — zsh completion for **rs3ctl** — cool-japan/rs3gw, the
#            **management CLI for the rs3gw (Rust S3 Gateway)** —
#            an ultra-lightweight, high-throughput, **S3-API-
#            compatible** object-storage gateway written in Rust.
#            rs3gw fronts heterogeneous storage backends (local
#            filesystem, NFSv4 mounts, S3 buckets on AWS / Wasabi /
#            Backblaze B2 / Cloudflare R2 / DigitalOcean Spaces /
#            MinIO / Ceph RADOS Gateway / SeaweedFS / Garage, NATS
#            object store, IPFS, etcd) and exposes them all through
#            a unified S3-compatible REST surface plus a typed
#            **GraphQL admin API** (built on the canonical Rust
#            GraphQL server library `async-graphql`) for management
#            operations (bucket CRUD, object CRUD, replication
#            policies, metrics, observability, maintenance, dataset-
#            preprocessing pipelines).  `rs3ctl` is the dedicated
#            command-line client for the GraphQL admin endpoint.
#            Rust=178 OPENING leg of new Axis 123 (GraphQL /
#            Facebook RFC GraphQL specification + GraphQL HTTP
#            transport + GraphQL Subscriptions) via the canonical
#            Rust GraphQL server library **async-graphql/async-
#            graphql**.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/cool-japan/rs3gw
#                  (rs3ctl is `src/bin/rs3ctl.rs` within the
#                   rs3gw workspace; the workspace also ships
#                   `rs3gw` (the gateway daemon), `testdata-
#                   generator` and `s3-migrate` companion bins)
#   Maintainer : COOLJAPAN OU / Team Kitasan
#   License    : Apache-2.0
